  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AHP Phase II Bangladesh Rohingya Crisis Humanitarian Response (BGD-0018)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project supports vulnerable communities - both Rohingya refugees and host communities - with an integrated and inclusive project consisting of: health (including sexual and reproductive health, mental health and psychosocial support), education, integrated protection, and water and sanitation health (WASH) services. The project involves building thousands of latrines and also seeking to influence design specifications for the humanitarian response in Rohinga, including improved sanitation facilities such as bio-fill latrines, twin pit latrine, effluent pit latrine, raised platform latrine and accessible and private women-friendly bathing spaces.</narrative>
  </description>
